INTERMEDIATE FAILURES PRESERVED

1. Initial format and lint checks failed on unformatted scaffold files and two import() type annotations in packages/db/src/outbox.ts. The import types were made explicit and the scaffold was formatted. The final aggregate gate passed.

2. The first root unit run followed workspace node_modules symlinks because the custom exclude list replaced Vitest defaults. It attempted Zod's package-source tests and reported 52 failed files, while 31,707 dependency tests ran. It also exposed a JSX transform error in the new Web component test. The root config now excludes node_modules/.next and sets OXC automatic JSX. The final project-only result is 9 files and 51 tests passed.

3. The first root Replay and offline checks could not resolve @onlyboth/challenge-catalog because the root package had not declared its workspace script dependencies. The dependencies were added explicitly; both final checks passed.

4. The first production build inferred `<home>` as the workspace root because an unrelated parent package-lock.json exists, then Turbopack encountered a protected parent directory. apps/web/next.config.ts now pins turbopack.root to this repository, with an integration regression test. The final build passed without the warning.

5. The first post-build offline check treated the official documentation URL in Next's generated next-env.d.ts comment as a remote runtime asset. Declaration files are now excluded from the runtime-source scan. Runtime TypeScript, TSX, and CSS remain covered; the final check reported zero external Web dependencies.

6. The first local route-smoke shell used zsh's read-only variable name "status" and exited 1 before making the route assertions. It was rerun with "http_code" and all five routes returned 200.

